Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Band, element of a mummy breast cover (right side) cut out and perforated, featuring two registers depicting two of the four sons of Horus, mummiform. At the top, Amset, and at the bottom, Qebehsenuf, both facing right. Black contours, brick-red background.
